{
  "name": "dct-webinar-nov-2002",
  "title": "Digital Consumer Technology: The Revolution Has Started \u2014 Aberdeen DCT Webinar Deck",
  "description": "Presentation slides from Aberdeen Group's November 1, 2002 DCT webinar. Three deep-dive sections: Mobile Convergence Devices (handset economics, network operator gatekeepers, 3G timing), Media Servers (desired functionality, emerging product classes from HP Media Center/Intel Media PC/Sony Cocoon/STB accessories, Media Center requirements), and Home Networking (eleven contending technologies, longer-term architecture with consumer-configurable gateway/firewall/VoIP/DRM, 5 GHz spectrum of choice). Closes with DCT Practice Services retainer package and contact for Peter Kastner. Complements the companion DCEIT v6 practice deck (dct-dceit-practice-v6-2002) and the pre-webinar promotional announcement (dct-webinar-announcement-2002-11).",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "created": "2026-04-19",
  "licenses": [
    {
      "name": "CC-BY-4.0",
      "path": "https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/"
    }
  ],
  "contributors": [
